& [LMStudioCorpusPrompt:boundary_delineation_010_retry_003] is a non-mutating SOP worker prompt packet
  + [task_family] is boundary_delineation
  + [prompt_boundary] is prompt-only, no tools, no file reads, no repo mutation, no hidden-state claims
  + [expected_output] is exactly one raw ASCII SOP node named InferenceJobResult with seven filled property lines and no Markdown
  + [validation_required_fields] is focus, inside, boundary, outside, inference, caution, next_step
  + [validation_required_terms] is focus, boundary, outside, caution
  + [validation_forbidden_terms] is repo mutation, hidden state access, project-root authority, completed integration
  + [retry_reason] is first run used operator substitution, retry 001 copied placeholders, and retry 002 produced filled but non-ASCII-noisy output
  + [prompt_text] is:
    You are performing a no-tools SOP inference job from this prompt only.
    Do not call tools, inspect files, mutate state, or claim repo authority.
    Codex owns launch, capture, validation, integration, commits, and pushes.

    SOP primer:
    & [Name] is a subject declaration.
    + [field] is a property or inferred field.
    The literal word is is the SOP property operator.
    When exact raw SOP is requested, every property line must use + [field] is value.
    Do not replace is with verbs such as separates, includes, reminds, lists, routes, or contains.
    Do not output ellipses, TODO, TBD, placeholder, or empty field content.
    Use ASCII only. Use normal hyphen -, straight apostrophe ', and straight quote " if punctuation is needed.
    (attention) :inside: /boundary/ |outside| means inside belongs in focus, boundary separates identity, and outside is uncertainty or out-of-scope material.

    Task family:
    boundary_delineation tests whether you can keep attention notation clean across a new subject.

    Subject to delineate:
    "a local model worker may propose non-mutating SOP text, but Codex remains the authority for integration."

    Return exactly these eight raw SOP lines and no extra text.
    Fill each field with a short specific ASCII phrase about the subject.
    Use this exact field order:
    & [InferenceJobResult] is boundary delineation proposal
      + [focus] is <specific focus phrase>
      + [inside] is <specific in-scope material>
      + [boundary] is <specific separating rule>
      + [outside] is <specific uncertainty or out-of-scope material>
      + [inference] is <specific conclusion>
      + [caution] is <specific caution>
      + [next_step] is <specific proposed next step>

    Final check before answering:
    Line 1 must start with &.
    Lines 2 through 8 must use exactly this operator form: two spaces, +, space, [field], space, is, space, value.
    Do not replace is with any other verb on any property line.
    Replace every bracketed placeholder with specific content.
    Use ASCII only and do not use curly quotes, nonbreaking hyphens, em dashes, or special punctuation.
    Include the literal terms focus, boundary, outside, and caution at least once.
    Do not claim repo mutation, hidden state access, project-root authority, or completed integration.
